    "We started by creating a matrix R c,t for each country and each topic, with retweeters as rows and news outlets as a column, whereas c 2 {France, Germany, Italy, UK} and t 2 {Brexit, Coronavirus, Covid Vaccine}.",
    "The entry r i,j of R c,t is the number of times user i retweeted a tweet posted by news source j based in the country c on topic t. We then computed the cosine similarity for each pair of columns to measure the audiences' similarity for each pair of news sources.",
    "Thus, the weight w a,b of the edge between node a and b in the graph G is equal to:",
    "where r a and r b are the two column vectors of news sources i and j, respectively.",
    "It should be noted that w a,b 2 [0, 1] since all the entries of the matrix are non-negative."
